  <heading>SMULH</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Signed multiply high</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>This instruction multiplies two 64-bit register values, and writes
bits[127:64] of the 128-bit result to the 64-bit destination register.</para>
    </authored>
  </desc>
  <operationalnotes>
    <operationalnote>
      <operationalnote_content>
        <para>This instruction is a data-independent-time instruction as described in <xref linkend="ARMARM_BEICCDDAB3">About PSTATE.DIT</xref>.</para>
      </operationalnote_content>
    </operationalnote>
  </operationalnotes>
